Hidden Clover Cake

Green Cake:
1 1/2 c ap flour
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp baking powder
1/2 c (1 stick) unsalted butter, softened
1 1/2 c sugar
1/4 c vegetable oil
1 tsp vanilla
2 eggs
1/2 c buttermilk
green food coloring

White Cake:
1 1/2 c ap flour
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 c (1 stick) unsalted butter
1 1/2 c sugar
1/4 c vegetable oil
1 tsp vanilla
2 eggs
1/2 c buttermilk

Preheat oven to 350F. Spray 13x9" pan with nonstick spray. In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, sal, baking powder and baking soda. Set aside. In the bowl of a stand mixer, beat the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Scrape down the sides and add the oil and vanilla, mixing to combine. Add the eggs one at a time. mixing well and scraping down the sides after each one. Add half the flour mixture and mix on low speed until incorporated, then stir in 1/4 c of buttermilk. Repeat to use the remaining flour and buttermilk. Add the food coloring as desired and stir to incoporate. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 25-30 min or until the top springs back when gently pressed. Let the green cake cool completely and refrigerate it until it feels firm to the touch, 2-3 hrs. Once it's chilled, us a shamrock cookie cutter to cut out cake pieces. Spray a 9x5 loaf pan with nonstick spray. In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Set aside. In the bowl of a stand mixer, beat the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Scrape down the sides and add the oil and vanilla, mixing to combine. Add the eggs one at a time, mixing well and scraping down the sides after each one. Add half the flour mixture and mix on low speed until incorporated, then stir in 1/4 c buttermilk. Repeat with the remaining flour and buttermilk. Pour a layer of batter on the bottom of the loaf pan, ~1/2" deep. Place green cake pieces in a row along the batter, making sure to align them all the same way. Carefully pour the remaining white batter over the shamrocks, using a spoon to get at the hard to reach places. Bake the cake for 1 hr, until the top is brown and a toothpick comes out clean. Let the cake cool in the loaf pan for 15 min, then invert onto a wire rack and let it cool completely before slicing and serving.
